nodes.title: About Number of Steps (My tests)
widgets_values:
Steps tested on I2V_bf16 model with large size 768p. and 5 seconds length.
More Steps = More time generating. Keep it in mind.

Cartoon/Anime: 
         ~20 Steps for a Draft/ Descent Quality
         ~30 Steps for Good Quality

Realism/Movie:
         ~20 Steps for Draft
         At least ~50 Steps for descent Quality
         ~100 Steps for amazing realistic video

**This is my >OPINION< based on my results and depents hearvly on what you're trying to generate!
This part will convert the image to dimensions that are multiples of 16p so that the generation is not rejected by the model.

nodes.title: About 2 Samplers
widgets_values: "Scheduled CFG Guidance" Splits the process in half, running the second half of it without cfg to make it faster without lose quality. Saves around 25% of the time Sampling.
You can Bypass "WanImageToVideo" node to use T2V Wan model without errors.

If you want to continue a video, Enable this group. It will take the last frame from a video and continue it!

1. Enable the "Load From Video" group.
2. Insert the video path in Load Video node.
    *In windows 11, Ctrl + Shift + C will copy the path of your file quickly.
3. Run the workflow.

**If you're running this workflow on cloud PC, you can replace the "Load Video (Path)" by "Load Video (Upload)".

nodes.title: Decode
widgets_values: If you don't have enough Ram, use the Tiled decoder. Just replace the connection of the IMAGE output in reroute.

nodes.title: Wan Img2Vid (Fast) + Video Extend + Upscale + Interpolation

widgets_values:
This is a simple Image2Video Workflow using Wan models.

0. >>>>> Update your ComfyUi! <<<<<

Downloading Models (Folders to place files are intuitive):
https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/Wan_2.1_ComfyUI_repackaged/tree/main/split_files

Downloading Fast Lora:
https://civitai.com/models/1585622/causvid-lora-massive-speed-up-for-wan21-made-by-kijai?modelVersionId=1794316
Place it in your Loras folder

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*Focus on the dark-green nodes. Most of basic inputs are defined in those nodes.
1. Load the image you wish to animate.
2. Define the long side of your video. The other side will be auto scaled based on this.
3. Define the length in seconds of the video
4. Define your positive and negative prompt.
5. Use the "Fast Groups Bypasser" to switch the options you want to use from this workflow.
6. Run the workflow!
